      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented quality management system; version control and release notes available.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 is a commercially released solver with a documented QMS. No failure modes have been observed in the solver's hemolysis-relevant modules across prior simulation campaigns conducted by this team."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes vendor-supplied benchmark suite for rotating machinery and scalar transport.",
      "rationale": "The solver vendor benchmark suite for rotating frame scalar transport was executed. No contraindications have been reported in the benchmark outputs, and the assessment team has not encountered any issues with code correctness for the turbulence and hemolysis damage models used."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for relative hemolysis index QoI on the fine-to-medium mesh pair.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 4.2 M cells, medium: 8.7 M cells, fine: 17.1 M cells). GCI for RHI between fine and medium grids is 3.2%, meeting the < 5% criterion. No failure modes have been observed during the convergence study iterations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate the 5 target flow-speed operating points within ±3% of nominal values; blood analog fluid properties documented.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental data were collected at flow rates of 2.5, 3.5, 4.5, 5.5, and 6.5 L/min at 2500 rpm using a glycerol-water blood analog. Measured operating points fall within ±2.1% of nominal CFD boundary conditions. No issues with test condition fidelity have been encountered across the dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RHI values fall within ±15% of experimental measurements at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RHI values compared against experimental normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) converted to RHI at all 5 operating points. Maximum deviation is 11.4% at the 6.5 L/min condition. No failure modes have been observed in the output comparison process."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "RHI is a recognized hemolysis QoI directly linked to the clinical acceptance criterion; power-law damage model parameters are literature-sourced.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index derived from the Giersiepen power-law damage model is the accepted QoI for CFD-based hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841. The QoI maps directly to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1. No contraindications to the relevance of RHI as a surrogate for clinical hemolysis have been reported in the literature reviewed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry is the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares rotary impeller topology and operating regime with the subject CPB device.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump geometry under identical flow-speed combinations as the COU operating envelope. The FDA pump shares impeller diameter, blade count, and RPM range with the subject device. No failure modes have been observed that would undermine the relevance mapping between the validation platform and the COU device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to at least 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All five operating-point simulations achieved residual convergence below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum. Mass imbalance across the rotating domain is below 0.005% in all cases. No issues with solver convergence or numerical instability have been encountered."
    },
